name: AbnormalPresentation
title: Abnormal Presentation
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of  values contains physical exam finding that represent a fetus in an abnormal position in the uterus at the time of delivery.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients with a fetus in an abnormal position in the uterus at the time of delivery.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Physical Exam" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Include ICD 9 CM codes that identify a fetus in an abnormal position.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that identify a fetus in a vertex presentation.)
